Johannesburg A 24-year-old man, who allegedly stabbed three people, one of them fatally, during a bar brawl was arrested and a blood stained knife was recovered from the suspect in the Ladysmith CBD, KwaZulu-Natal police said on Monday. &quot;On Friday evening, one of the three was fatally stabbed at Plaza Centre and was declared dead on the scene. The others were taken for medical treatment,&quot; police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said. Zwane said police responded quickly and they traced the man to a building in the CBD. &quot;The suspect faces a charge of murder, assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm as well carrying a dangerous weapon and he is due to appear in the Ladysmith Magistrate's Court on Monday,&quot; Zwane said. The 29-year-old deceased has not yet been identified. African News Agency